#Reads data in using data.table package allowing for use of qqman to make plots and dplyr to filter and format
##Summary Statistics are from https://www.ebi.ac.uk/gwas/studies/GCST004132 using the FTP Download in the harmonised folder.
data = fread("28067908-GCST004132-EFO_0000384.h.tsv")
###Reads in the data and arranages it using dpylr package and write the newly formatted file into a new file locuszoom.assoc.liner. This new formatting will allow it to be used on https://my.locuszoom.org
locuszoom = arrange(data, chromosome, base_pair_location)
fwrite(locuszoom, file="locuszoom.assoc.liner")

#Run using terminal not R
##Uses https://github.com/bulik/ldsc in order to find the Observed scale heritibility of cronhs diesease using the summary statistcs
#Activates conda enviroment
conda activate ldsc
#formats the input summary statistics into the nessecary order and headings to be analyzed by ldsc.py by passing it flags for what the columns are originally named.
munge_sumstats.py --sumstats /home/fsalgado/28067908-GCST004132-EFO_0000384.h.tsv --N 40266 --out /home/fsalgado/crohns --merge-alleles /home/data/HW5_data/w_hm3.snplist --snp variant_id --p p_value --a1 effect_allele --a2 other_allele
##runs the now formatted summary statistics against European LD scores from https://alkesgroup.broadinstitute.org/LDSCORE/
ldsc.py --h2 crohns.sumstats.gz --ref-ld-chr /home/data/HW5_data/eur_w_ld_chr/ --w-ld-chr /home/data/HW5_data/eur_w_ld_chr/ --out crohns_h2

##table of Observed scale h2 and Standard error | Trait | Observed scale h2 | se | | :â€” | â€”: | â€”: | | Crohnâ€™s |0.4172 |0.044 |

Note that the echo = FALSE parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.

#Run using terminal not R
##Uses SPrediXan avalible at https://github.com/hakyimlab/MetaXcan in order to find genes that are significantly enriched with SNPs based on the summary statistics. Model database used are from https://predictdb.org/.
##This must be done in a conda enviroment using the imlabtools provided from https://github.com/hakyimlab/MetaXcan 
conda deactivate
conda activate imlabtools
## SprediXcan is passed the data base files for analysis of Stomach tissues and the column headers of info it needs based on their name in the summary statistics
SPrediXcan.py --model_db_path /home/data/predixcan_models/en_Stomach.db --covariance /home/data/predixcan_models/en_Stomach.txt.gz --gwas_file /home/fernando-jared/28067908-GCST004132-EFO_0000384.h.tsv --snp_column variant_id --effect_allele_column effect_allele --non_effect_allele_column other_allele --pvalue_column p_value --beta_column beta --output_file predixcan_crohns_Stomach.csv
#Reads in and creats a table of the most significant genes found from the SPredXican of the stomach tissue
pred_stom = fread("predixcan_crohns_Stomach.csv")
#arranges the file by largest p-value
Pstom = arrange(pred_stom,pvalue)
Pstom
